snippet.textDisplay:
Did the people of the island have a say in this decision to go ahead with the fucked up useless airport?

Interesting topic I knew nothing about. But a terrible act of vandalistic journalism by “drinking the cool aid” and not trying to hold anyone to account for a terrible decision that may have cost this island it’s financial independence, and guaranteed financial dependence and servitude. Whom would that benefit? “Follow the money” is what you should always do as journalists, and @Wendover Productions is a total fucking failure here

Was there no other place on the island to put the airport? Was there no other way to orientate the runway? Assuming there were options, why was no study of the winds? If there was NO options for the runway, why was there no study of the winds?

The ONLY reason one can believe there was no study of the winds, was that someone KNEW that such a study would kill the project. THAT person should be in jail and THAT is what the documentary should be about, not this fucked up sugar coated feel good film about a fucked up bureaucratic decision that was made by whom?

snippet.textDisplay:
Any st Helena residents reading this please tell me what it’s like living there, so interesting!
1. What’s it like living so isolated from anywhere else
2. What’s the community like, it seems like there’s loads of cultural diversity in religion and ethnicity, living in a pretty homogeneous part of Britain, I’m really interested in how these cultures coalesce. Do some cultures and traditions get borrowed from other cultures due to proximity?
Where I live, we don’t really have much of a community at all, we mostly try to keep away from each other as much as possible!
